<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.413St4/32.</note>
                        <head>[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-20"><hi rend="italic">June 20,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Reports that September 2 is proposed by the Emperor as the date for the
                            presentation of the statue of Gen. von Steuben; also that the
                            appointment of C. P. Wolfram as special representative of the President
                            is agreeable to the German Emperor.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>